Description:
BAY VIEWS ! SWIMMING POOL ! LARGE BLOCK !
Positioned in a quiet court location with quality homes surrounding this immaculate 3 bedroom home offers so much for money. If you love entertaining or just relaxing with minimal maintenance you will absolutely appreciate this backyard with extensive timber decking of walkways and sun lounge areas, gazebo and pool. The property is situated on a block approx.. 935 sq.m. with circular driveway, plenty of room for caravan, boat or extra vehicles and yard is fully fenced.

An inspection on this property is a MUST.

Address: 469 Mt Wellington Road French Island VIC 3921
Description:
Exclusive private island hideaway.
A uniquely private island hideaway less than two hours from Melbourne and light years from the stresses of city life, experience the rural charm and quiet isolation that is Beauciel. Maintained as a working farm with an organic fruit and vegetable garden and capacity to run sheep and cattle, no expense has been spared in creating this idyllic French Island retreat set on 50 acres (approx). Boasting sweeping views of Western Port Bay from one of the highest points on the island, the sprawling timber residence offers farmhouse-style luxury with four bedrooms, two bathrooms, a big country kitchen, slow-combustion pot belly stove and a huge living and dining area opening onto a north-facing deck. The master suite includes French doors onto a private deck, a walk-in robe and ensuite, while gleaming pacific beech timber floors feature throughout the extensively renovated and extended home. A walled garden made from rustic corrugated iron and reclaimed century-old pier timbers providing a sheltered environment for espaliered apples, peaches and other fruits together with vegetables and ornamental vines all organically grown and watered by a drip system fed from a bore. Large rainwater storage tanks and a sophisticated solar, wind and back-up diesel generator system add to the property's self-sufficiency, with much of the equipment housed in a cleverly restored chicory kiln. All the land has been has been recently fenced, new cattle yards constructed, dams excavated and pastures kept free of super phosphates and other fertilisers not conducive to organic farming. Get away from it all and enjoy total privacy, yet still be close to town with regular daily ferry and barge services.

Description:
TURN YOUR HOBBY FARM FANTASY INTO REALITY
"BARRALLIER"
Named after French Explorer Francis Barrallier, is this unique, premium acreage, complete with quality soil, new livestock-yards, fencing, gates and dams.
Positioned centrally with views over Westernport Bay and beyond, this fantastic farm site of approx. 48 acres awaits your dream home, (stpa) maybe high on the hill, or hidden away, enjoying all the beauty nature has to offer.
French Island is approximately two thirds national park and is unincorporated, therefore is not governed by a local council, so no council rates apply. Being off the grid, means there are no power companies to deal with and no water rates to pay. About an hour from Melbourne, but like stepping back in time, we are a small community of around 100 residents, accessible by passenger ferry from Stony Point, or vehicle barge from Corinella.
Contact Phil on 5980 1234 to discuss this unique opportunity.

Description:
80 ACRES WITH MANY USES.
Beautiful rolling landscape, well treed and drained, a model farm that lends itself to any form of agriculture.
Fenced to 8 Paddocks all watered and sheltered, 2 Dams, stock bore, Hay Shed and Tractor Shed.
Water tanks holding 100,000 Litres, 12m X 12m lock up colorbond garage, 35m X 20m shed with Mechanics Pit.
- 3 Bedrooms plus Office/Study. Master has ensuite.
- Tasmanian Oak Kitchen with walk in pantry.
- Large Family room and Lounge.
- In ground Pool, Salt Chlorinated.
- 5kw Solar @ 60c Kilowatt.
This is already producing quality beef cattle from the improved pastures and with a sandy loam is ideal for Flowers or Veggies.
Great family home with plenty of shedding for storage, mechanical or car collectors you are set up for the future.
Inspections will not disapoint. To inspect immediately call Colin Butler.

Description:
SOLD BY PHIL BOCK WITHIN ONE WEEK OF LISTING!!!
Haven of natural flora and fauna, with all the work done to provide everything you need to eat, sleep and live FULLY OFF GRID, with no council rates, no nearby neighbours and no pollution! Say goodbye to power bills forever.
This fully established open plan, Loft-Cottage paradise of natural beauty may not be the Ritz, but many would agree it's better, given the fully established and netted herb and vegetable garden, complete with comprehensive orchard to provide you with quality food, more conveniently and probably more fresh than any supermarket could ever supply.
Almost too many fruits and vegetables to list, Avocado, bayleaf, blueberry, cherry, coriander, gooseberry, grape, grapefruit, kaffir-lime, lemon, licorice, lime, loganberry, nectarine, orange, passionfruit, peach, pear, plum, potato, prune, raspberry, rhubarb, strawberry and tangelo.
Also includes: Fully equipped power system including wind-turbine, solar panels, inverter and generator, wood-stove/oven, Rotaloo, 50,000 litres of rainwater storage plus dam, decks, sunroom and open-living area with spiral staircase to your boudoir.
Call French Islands only local real estate representative Phil Bock on: 0438 497 715

Description:
Your Dream 25 Acre Property!!
A rare opportunity exists to acquire your dream 'Acreage' property at an affordable price! This well-established 25 Acre property is within 5km to the Lang Lang town ship, also having easy access to the South Gippsland Highway and only 25 minutes from the Pakenham town ship.
The comfortable brick veneer home comprises of 4 bedrooms (master with ensuite), family room with combustion heating, separate dining, formal lounge room, kitchen with wall oven, electric hotplates and range hood. Also on offer is a one bedroom bungalow featuring lounge room.
Outside, the property is divided into 6 main paddocks, cattle ramp, double garage and hay shed.
This is certainly your chance to get into the exclusive acreage market! Do not delay or you may miss out!

Description:
City Class meets Country Tranquility
This brilliant three- bedroom family home situated in a quiet court location is sure to turn heads! Boasting with large open plan living perfectly suited for the growing family.
A stunning, light filled and renovated central kitchen offers contemporary pendant down lights,spacious Ceaser stone bench tops, soft close cupboards and draws, dishwasher, gas cook-top with range hood and a large double door stainless steel fridge to stay! Overlooking a modern living area with a wood feature built-in TV cabinet to compliment the cutting edge finish to this property.
A generous master suite with walk-in robe, leading edge wallpaper feature and stunning ensuite is well situated away from the remaining bedrooms. Bedrooms two and three have built-in robes and plenty of space for the kids to play! A freshly renovated family bathroom provides a gorgeous wood feature wall and rainfall shower head.
The large newly built outdoor decking to the rear yard will provide a year round, all season excuse to entertain! The built in BBQ and esky are sure to be a hit this summer.
Set at the front of a large 846sqm block this property screams summer fun with plenty of space for backyard cricket!
Additional features include;
- Enclosed rear yard with newly built timber gate
- Enough space for the boat or 5-6 car spaces
- "Black Butt" floating floor boards throughout as seen on "The Block" TV program.
- Split System heat and cooling
- Gas Ducted heating on Natural Gas
- LED down lights throughout
- Potential subdivision (S.T.C.A)
- Two erected garden sheds to the rear yard
Make the most of this wonderful opportunity to secure a freshly renovated, city class property located in the quiet Lang Lang location!

Description:
Magical Waterfront With Private Jetty
As you step onto this magnificent rural coastal property you are surrounded by mature native trees and shrubs and an abundance of birds and wildlife that surround the substantial main residence and guest cottage.
Perfect for a weekender or a cozy retreat the well built double storey 3 bedroom mud brick home sits on 14 acres of bush and grassland and is very spoilt with its own private jetty. The home features huge picture windows overlooking the water, a spacious open plan layout and a rustic Baltic pine kitchen with an adjoining preparation kitchen and old style pantry.
The main bedroom has a large walk-in robe and adjoins the family bathroom. The large 3rd bedroom is upstairs and has extensive views of the water and all the way to Phillip Island.
The extensive shedding can house cars, boats, caravans and tractors and is ideal for a home business or handyman.
The five well watered paddocks would suit most livestock including horses and cattle.
The single bedroom guest cottage overlooks the Bass River and is an adventure playground for sailing, fishermen, artists and kayaking.
This is a beautiful, unique and magical place where life revolves around the water and bush and although only one hour from the city, it feels a million miles from everything.

Description:
FIRST HOME OR INVESTMENT PROPERTY
Whether you're buying your first home or adding to your investment portfolio this is the right property for you. Approx. 3 years old and close to schools and parks this property has size and location in its favour. Featuring:
- 3 bedrooms, Master with ensuite and walk-in robe
- The modern kitchen has stainless steel appliances including a dishwasher and the 600mm under-bench oven has a natural gas cooktop.
- 2 Living areas - Formal lounge and separate dining area both of which have a split-system reverse-cycle heating and cooling unit.
- There's a double garage and garden shed as well as a large courtyard
If you're just starting out in the property market this is an excellent first home or the perfect home if you're looking to downsize. But investors will also be pleased because the location of this home is close to all shops and schools - just a short walk away. So, call Glenda Ashton today to make a time to inspect this property.
